          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682354229942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, then pulse until everything is finely chopped</p><p>Once finely chopped, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Pulse until everything is blitzed but not smooth – this is your <strong>falafel mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682354233884-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
