            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> tahini </strong>to a small bowl<strong> </strong>with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>warm water </strong>and mix until fully combined and smooth</p><p>Add your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a fan of raw garlic? Just add a little!) a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a squeeze of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon juice</strong>, then stir it all together – this is your <strong>tahini yoghurt</strong></p><p>Once the falafel have been cooking for 15 min, add your <strong>wholemeal pitta[s]</strong> to the other side of the baking tray and return the tray to the oven for 3-4 min further or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
